title: Grateful Dead Live at Pine Knob Music Theater on 1991-06-20
lineage: mac > Tascam 122b > Tascam HD-P2 > wav 24/48 > Adobe Audition 1.5 > Wavelab 6 with iZotope Ozone  4 > iZotope RX Advanced > wav 16/44.1 > CD Wave > Flac 16 Taped by Gregg Holtz, from front of OTS, DFC
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Gray, Greatest Story Ever Told, Peggy-O, Mexicali Blues > Maggie's Farm, Bird Song

Set 2

Throwing Stones > Iko Iko, All Along The Watchtower > Standing On The Moon > He's Gone > Drums > Space > The Wheel > I Need A Miracle > Wharf Rat > Throwing Stones > Not Fade Away 

E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text:
Great sound, very good show I am giving the five star rating so that you will check this out.  The sound is exceptional and with Bruce H. in the fold, the music is top notch.  
Of course this does not deserve the same rating as 2-13-70 or 8-27-72, but it does deserve to be enjoyed at high volumes.

so-so This is a great recording that documents a tepid performance of an interesting set list. The recording gets 5 stars. If we limit the judgement of the performance to Drums & Space, it would get 5 stars as well.

The perfomance gets 3 stars, and that is being rather generous.
During Peggy o I would have jumped on stage and kicked the accordian out of bruces overeager paws.
PHIL Phil's bass is so sick on Throwing Stones!!!!
